This paper proposes a method for reinforcement learning using spiking neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks and learning (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of Q-learning algorithm, which is a popular reinforcement learning algorithm and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of random connections and feed-forward networks, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the potential for energy efficiency in neuromorphic hardware, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO).
